Data

For this project, we used US GDP quarterly dataset from 1947 to 2020. The dataset is download from https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/GDPC1

Exploratory Anlyaisis

Load dataset

gdp_df<-read.csv("GDPC1.csv")
gdp_ts<-ts(gdp_df$GDPC1,frequency=4,start=c(1947,1))
head(gdp_ts)
##          Qtr1     Qtr2     Qtr3     Qtr4
## 1947 2033.061 2027.639 2023.452 2055.103
## 1948 2086.017 2120.450

Visualize dataset

autoplot(gdp_ts)

Stablize variance

lambda<-BoxCox.lambda(gdp_ts)
transform_gdp<-BoxCox(gdp_ts,lambda=lambda)
autoplot(transform_gdp)

Split train and test dataset

train_gdp<-window(transform_gdp,end=c(2009,4))
test_gdp<-window(transform_gdp,start=c(2010,1))

Model Construction

ETS Model

ets_model<-ets(train_gdp)
ets_model
## ETS(A,Ad,N) 
## 
## Call:
##  ets(y = train_gdp) 
## 
##   Smoothing parameters:
##     alpha = 0.9999 
##     beta  = 0.5183 
##     phi   = 0.8577 
## 
##   Initial states:
##     l = 8.9798 
##     b = 9e-04 
## 
##   sigma:  0.0139
## 
##       AIC      AICc       BIC 
## -754.7013 -754.3584 -733.5247
checkresiduals(ets_model)

## 
##  Ljung-Box test
## 
## data:  Residuals from ETS(A,Ad,N)
## Q* = 18.544, df = 3, p-value = 0.0003396
## 
## Model df: 5.   Total lags used: 8
ets_fc<-forecast(ets_model,h=42)
autoplot(train_gdp) + autolayer(ets_fc,series="ETS forecast")

accuracy(ets_fc,test_gdp)

ARIMA Model

arima_model<-auto.arima(train_gdp)
arima_model
## Series: train_gdp 
## ARIMA(1,1,2) with drift 
## 
## Coefficients:
##          ar1     ma1     ma2   drift

## s.e.  0.1834  0.1798  0.0776  0.0014
## 
## sigma^2 estimated as 0.0001697:  log likelihood=735.56
## AIC=-1461.11   AICc=-1460.87   BIC=-1443.49
checkresiduals(arima_model)

## 
##  Ljung-Box test
## 
## data:  Residuals from ARIMA(1,1,2) with drift
## Q* = 6.7638, df = 4, p-value = 0.1489
## 
## Model df: 4.   Total lags used: 8
arima_fc<-forecast(arima_model,h=42)
autoplot(train_gdp) + autolayer(arima_fc,series="ETS forecast")
